Our bodies are our temples. We are not less but more like Heavenly
Father because we are embodied. I testify that we are His children,
made in His image, with the potential to become like Him. Let us treat
this divine gift of the body with great care. Someday, if we are worthy,
we shall receive a perfected, glorious body--pure and clean like my new
little granddaughter, only inseparably bound to the spirit. And we shall
shout for joy (see  Job 38:7) to receive this gift again for which we
have longed (see D&C 138:50). May we respect the sanctity of the body
during mortality so that the Lord may sanctify and exalt it for eternity.
     -- Susan W. Tanner
