The standard is clear. If something we think, see, hear, or do distances
us from the Holy Ghost, then we should stop thinking, seeing, hearing,
or doing that thing. If that which is intended to entertain, for
example, alienates us from the Holy Spirit, then certainly that type of
entertainment is not for us. Because the Spirit cannot abide that which
is vulgar, crude, or immodest, then clearly such things are not for us.
Because we estrange the Spirit of the Lord when we engage in activities
we know we should shun, then such things definitely are not for us.
     -- David A Bednar
